narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, absolutely. Learning about the Global South was fascinating--it's not every day that a student thinks about the Anglophone Caribbean and South Africa in the same context of queer identity. Also, Andrew is a great professor. He is deeply invested in the material and really cares about your general wellbeing as a student. 10/10.
Yes, in part because it's one of the only classes offered at Yale that touches on this material, but also because it's a great class to explore an often forgotten region.
